<Programs Use="Context">
<Program Use="Context" Name="MainProgram">
<Routines Use="Context">
<Routine Use="Target" Name="DeviceLogic" Type="RLL">
<Description>
<![CDATA[Process the logic for each device with index and indirect addressing.]]>
</Description>
<RLLContent>
<Rung Number="0" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[One 1st scan set DeviceNum (index/pointer) to 0]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[XIC(S:FS)MOV(0,dNum);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="1" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[Convert the start delay time to milliseconds]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[MUL(Device[dNum].StartDelayms,1000,Device[dNum].StartDelay.PRE);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="2" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[Convert the timed run target time to milliseconds]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[MUL(Device[dNum].TimedRunTarget,1000,Device[dNum].TimedRunTargetms);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="3" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[This logic controls the run / stop for FT103 when running in Auto and Manual]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[[XIC(Device[dNum].AutoMan) XIC(Device[dNum].AutoRun) XIC(Device[dNum].PermissivesAuto) ,XIO(Device[dNum].AutoMan) XIC(Device[dNum].ManualRun) XIC(Device[dNum].PermissivesMan) ]XIC(StartBeepTimer.DN)TON(Device[dNum].StartDelay,?,?);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="4" Type="N">
<Text>
<![CDATA[XIC(HMI_RecipeStart)ONS(Device[dNum].OneShots[3])OTL(Device[dNum].AutoRun);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="5" Type="N">
<Text>
<![CDATA[XIO(HMI_RecipeStart)ONS(Device[dNum].OneShots[4])OTU(Device[dNum].AutoRun);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="6" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[Start device and reset and start the  device cycle timer, run campaign timer and total timer]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[XIC(Device[dNum].StartDelay.DN)[XIC(AllDeviceEnable) XIO(Device[dNum].Interlock) OTE(Device[dNum].Output) ,[RTO(Device[dNum].CycleTime,?,?) RTO(Device[dNum].TotalTime,?,?) ,ONS(Device[dNum].OneShots[0]) RES(Device[dNum].CycleTime) ] ];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="7" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[If any device in placed into manaul run - set the AnyManualRun bit to trigger pre-start beep]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[XIC(Device[dNum].ManualRun)[OTL(AnyManualRun) ,OTL(AnyManRunFlag) ];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="8" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[If any device in placed into Auto run - set the AnyManualRun bit to trigger pre-start beep]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[XIC(Device[dNum].AutoRun)[OTL(AnyAutoRun) ,OTL(AnyAutoRunFlag) ];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="9" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[Timed Run or Campaing Time Run Logic - Logic to clear Campaign Timer on timed run enable and increment the campaign (Camp) timer when the device in running a timed run]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[XIC(Device[dNum].TimeRunEnable)[ONS(Device[dNum].OneShots[1]) OTL(Device[dNum].AutoMan) RES(Device[dNum].CampTime) ,XIC(Device[dNum].Output) RTO(Device[dNum].CampTime,?,?) ];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="10" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[Timed Run or Campaing Time Run Logic - if campaign timer greater than target or timed run bit off - stop the timed run logic and reset all to manual and idle]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[XIC(Device[dNum].TimeRunEnable)GRT(Device[dNum].CampTime.ACC,Device[dNum].TimedRunTargetms)ONS(RecipeStart)OTE(AllReset);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="11" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[Interlock all devices running in  Auto Run and Turn then off when an interlcok from any other device running in Auto Run is triggered]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[XIC(Device[dNum].AutoRun)XIC(Device[dNum].AutoMan)XIC(Auto_Run_All_Interlock)[OTL(Device[dNum].Interlock) ,OTU(Device[dNum].AutoRun) ];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="12" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[Reset AutoMan, AutoRun, TimeRunEnable, and HIMI_ReceipStart on PLC or HMI All_Rest]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[[XIC(AllReset) ,XIC(HMI_AllReset) ][OTU(Device[dNum].AutoMan) OTU(Device[dNum].AutoRun) OTU(Device[dNum].ManualRun) ,OTU(Device[dNum].TimeRunEnable) OTU(HMI_RecipeStart) ];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="13" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[increment index by one]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[ADD(dNum,1,dNum);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="14" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[Reset the device index when max device number is reached.  If AnyManRunFlag or AnyAutoRunFlag is not set - unlatch the corresponding AnyManualRun or AnyAutoRun bits - this is all for pre-start beep control (so the system only beeps when something is starting, not each time a new device starts) - Also resets Run Flags for next iteration through devices]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[GRT(dNum,13)[[MOV(0,dNum) ,[XIO(AnyManRunFlag) OTU(AnyManualRun) ,XIO(AnyAutoRunFlag) OTU(AnyAutoRun) ] ] ,OTU(AnyManRunFlag) OTU(AnyAutoRunFlag) ];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="15" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[Reset All Reset and HMI All Rest after scanning all devices]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[XIC(alwaysOFF)OTU(AllReset);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="16" Type="N">
<Text>
<![CDATA[XIC(alwaysOFF)OTE(TestBit1);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
</RLLContent>
</Routine>
</Routines>
</Program>
</Programs>
</Controller>
</RSLogix5000Content>
